      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "Interesting to know is that according to par 5.1.3 in <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/third_edition/html/conversions.html#189955\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">java.sun.com/docs/books/jls/third_edition/html/&hellip;</a> (The Java Language Spec): Despite the fact that overflow, underflow, or other loss of information may occur, narrowing conversions among primitive types never result in a run-time exception (&#167;11)."
