      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Note the types. Its not a primitive <code>long</code> here. Its the reference type <code>Long</code> which cant directly cast to an primitive <code>int</code>. <code>int y = (int)x;</code> will throws an execption but <code>int y = (int)(long)x</code> will work. (The reason is autoboxing)"
