    "answer_id" : 36331461,
    "question_id" : 4355303,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since Java 8\nyou can use: Math.toIntExact(long value)</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Math.html#toIntExact-long-\">See JavaDoc: Math.toIntExact</a></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Returns the value of the long argument; throwing an exception if the value overflows an int.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Source code of <code>Math.toIntExact</code> in JDK 8:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int toIntExact(long value) {\n    if ((int)value != value) {\n        throw new ArithmeticException(\"integer overflow\");\n    }\n    return (int)value;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
